	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You scatter red sand by blowing it over a torch or other kindling, creating a bright flame. The flame never uses oxygen or consumes the fire's fuel.</em></p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><p>You select a space with flammable material. You cannot directly set a creature on fire with this spell.</p><ul><li><p>You light a fire which does not spread and which cannot be smothered or quenched by mundane means. The fire spreads dim light in a 60 ft. radius and bright light in a 30 ft. radius. Undying torches can be made with this spell.</p></li><li><p>A creature that is within the area of effect of the fire when it appears takes damage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Area Hazard:</strong> The fire is permanent. Targets roll a save when they enter or when they end their turn in the well (but only once per turn).</p></li></ul><p><strong>Dexterity</strong> <strong>Save</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 3d6 fire]] damage.*</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage</p></li></ul><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 1d6 fire]] for each spell level above 2nd.</p><p><em>Normally, the only way to end a Continual Flame spell is with <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.oZwKW3I3yzrSdpLE]{Dispel Magic}</em> or a <em>@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-spells.Item.7dewwmP7KmxvlfKf]{Darkness}</em> spell.</em></p>",
			"chat": ""
		},
